  "synthesis_conclusions": [
    "Beta heterogeneity is assessed through deterministic geometry modulation, not formal variance partitioning. With n=4 valid fits (n_sign_gated=3), ANOVA-style decomposition is statistically meaningless (standard error on variance > 100% of estimate).",
    "",
    "Beta scatter statistics (n=4): Fitted beta spans a factor of 5.3 (log STD = 0.301 dex). Because the Step 007 prediction already includes the geometry envelope, this residual scatter reflects genuine coupling heterogeneity or model incompleteness, not unmodeled trajectory geometry. With n <= 4, formal variance partitioning is statistically meaningless.",
    "",
    "Full-catalog detection pattern (n=12): The Step 007 deterministic prediction at \u03b2_ref = 10\u207b\u2074 correctly classifies 9/12 flybys (accuracy 75.00%)\u20141 true positive, 8 true negatives, 3 false negatives, 0 false positives. Only NEAR exceeds the 0.5 mm/s detection threshold at \u03b2_ref; Galileo 1990, Rosetta 2005, and Cassini are false negatives because their predicted magnitudes at \u03b2_ref fall below threshold while the published anomalies are detections. All published nulls are correctly predicted as null. No false positives are present.",
    "",
    "Rank correlation across the full catalog (n=12): Spearman rho = 0.73 (p = 0.008) between predicted and observed anomaly magnitudes. This indicates moderate rank agreement.",
    "",
    "Sample-size caveat: Formal variance decomposition requires n >= 10 for reliable power. The current dataset (n=4) is insufficient. The dominant formal heterogeneity statistic remains Cochran Q / I^2 on the gated beta fits (Step 008).",
    "",
    "The 5.3x spread in gated fitted beta is consistent with geometry- and environment-dependent modulation of the effective coupling within the TEP framework. The envelope factors are pre-specified from trajectory geometry and independently measured plasma profiles; they are not tuned to reduce beta scatter."
  ],
